1
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:34,040
PREVIOUS EPISODE

2
00:02:37,760 --> 00:02:39,280
Let Puna carry it inside.

3
00:02:39,360 --> 00:02:41,240
-I'll help with that.
-No need.

4
00:02:42,360 --> 00:02:44,240
Right now, the boss
can't stand the sight of you.

5
00:02:45,280 --> 00:02:46,360
Stay away.

6
00:02:47,440 --> 00:02:48,320
Puna.

7
00:02:51,200 --> 00:02:52,360
Can you help with my outfit?

8
00:02:54,400 --> 00:02:56,120
Then, I'll go change first.

9
00:02:56,960 --> 00:02:57,800
Okay.

10
00:03:02,040 --> 00:03:03,120
I've called the fire truck.

11
00:03:04,160 --> 00:03:06,520
Everyone's helping to put out the fire,
doing what they can.

12
00:03:06,600 --> 00:03:10,080
Then hurry! Everyone, help! Come on!

13
00:03:10,880 --> 00:03:12,200
Why do you care?

14
00:03:39,880 --> 00:03:40,840
What's up, Chaiya?

15
00:03:43,480 --> 00:03:45,160
Alright, I'll tell you later.

16
00:03:45,840 --> 00:03:47,360
Okay, I'm on my way now.

17
00:03:52,360 --> 00:03:53,640
-Mr. Sonrak.
-Yes?

18
00:03:55,640 --> 00:03:58,480
Here's your water. Drink some cold water.

19
00:03:58,560 --> 00:04:01,360
Thank you so much. Leave it here for now.

20
00:04:01,440 --> 00:04:02,480
Just put it here.

21
00:04:03,880 --> 00:04:05,400
I'm so sorry. I didn't mean to.

22
00:04:05,480 --> 00:04:07,160
No, it's fine.

23
00:04:07,240 --> 00:04:09,200
Is it damaged?

24
00:04:09,280 --> 00:04:10,560
-Let me do it.
-Oh no.

25
00:04:10,640 --> 00:04:11,720
I'm sorry.

26
00:04:13,240 --> 00:04:14,640
It's an expensive bag.

27
00:04:14,720 --> 00:04:15,960
It's fine.

28
00:04:16,720 --> 00:04:19,880
Do you need help?
Let's see if water got into the bag.

29
00:04:20,480 --> 00:04:23,000
Is there any damage?

30
00:04:31,840 --> 00:04:33,280
What are you looking for?

31
00:04:34,920 --> 00:04:36,880
-The money.
-Huh?!

32
00:04:38,480 --> 00:04:41,040
-Is the money gone, Mr. Sonrak?
-Oh no!

33
00:04:41,120 --> 00:04:43,000
-His money is gone!
-Where did the money go?

34
00:04:43,880 --> 00:04:44,760
What's going on?

35
00:04:45,920 --> 00:04:46,920
The money's gone?

36
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:48,200
Yes.

37
00:04:48,280 --> 00:04:50,640
The money in Mr. Sonrak's bag is gone.

38
00:04:50,720 --> 00:04:54,400
It probably disappeared
in the chaos during the fire.

39
00:04:54,480 --> 00:04:55,800
That's right.

40
00:04:57,720 --> 00:04:59,360
Does this mean
there's a thief in the company?

41
00:05:01,840 --> 00:05:04,560
Chang! Chang!

42
00:05:06,440 --> 00:05:07,840
Yes, Mr. Singha? What's the matter?

43
00:05:07,920 --> 00:05:09,320
Sonrak's money is missing.

44
00:05:10,320 --> 00:05:13,040
Search everyone in the company!

45
00:05:14,920 --> 00:05:16,480
Understood, sir.

46
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:25,720
There's nothing. Why would I take it?

47
00:05:26,480 --> 00:05:27,960
I don't even have fake boobs yet!

48
00:05:28,560 --> 00:05:29,880
You can search me.

49
00:05:31,760 --> 00:05:33,920
-Stay still.
-What?

50
00:05:34,520 --> 00:05:37,000
I said there's nothing. There's nothing.

51
00:05:45,280 --> 00:05:47,360
Luckily we managed
to put the fire out in time.

52
00:05:47,440 --> 00:05:50,120
We're lucky the costume room
didn't catch fire.

53
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:53,560
Are those new clothes?
I've never seen them before.

54
00:05:53,640 --> 00:05:55,360
Yeah, they're from the sponsor.

55
00:05:55,440 --> 00:05:56,520
Alright.

56
00:06:03,880 --> 00:06:04,760
Hey.

57
00:06:06,360 --> 00:06:07,400
I need to search everyone.

58
00:06:08,160 --> 00:06:10,160
Mr. Sonrak's money is missing.

59
00:06:15,320 --> 00:06:16,360
Nothing.

60
00:06:21,760 --> 00:06:23,680
-What?
-Come here.

61
00:06:23,760 --> 00:06:26,200
Hey, I didn't take anything.

62
00:06:27,240 --> 00:06:28,600
Stay still.

63
00:06:35,400 --> 00:06:36,360
Whose bag is this?

64
00:06:37,120 --> 00:06:38,080
It's mine.

65
00:06:48,320 --> 00:06:49,840
All this money,

66
00:06:50,600 --> 00:06:51,760
is it yours, Puna?

67
00:06:55,280 --> 00:06:56,240
No.

68
00:06:56,320 --> 00:06:59,200
How did this money get in my bag?
I don't know anything about it.

69
00:06:59,280 --> 00:07:01,800
Mr. Singha, I found the money!

70
00:07:01,880 --> 00:07:02,760
Who?

71
00:07:03,800 --> 00:07:05,240
Who is the thief?

72
00:07:05,320 --> 00:07:06,400
It's Puna.

73
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:09,040
I found the money in her bag.

74
00:07:09,800 --> 00:07:10,840
Give it to me.

75
00:07:12,880 --> 00:07:13,840
Is this your money?

76
00:07:15,160 --> 00:07:16,960
It looks like it, Dad.

77
00:07:21,720 --> 00:07:23,920
My company doesn't employ thieves.

78
00:07:25,240 --> 00:07:28,160
Pack your bag and go home. You're fired!

79
00:07:29,840 --> 00:07:32,400
But I really didn't steal
Mr. Sonrak's money.

80
00:07:32,480 --> 00:07:34,440
I'll swear anywhere if you want.

81
00:07:38,840 --> 00:07:40,400
Dad, Puna didn't steal the money.

82
00:07:40,480 --> 00:07:41,600
How do you know?

83
00:07:45,520 --> 00:07:47,480
And how did the money end up in her bag?

84
00:07:49,960 --> 00:07:51,880
Well, I'm…

85
00:07:51,960 --> 00:07:54,000
I'm one who put the money in her bag.

86
00:07:54,080 --> 00:07:55,680
-What?
-That's not true!

87
00:07:55,760 --> 00:07:58,480
You didn't put the money in her bag.

88
00:08:02,480 --> 00:08:05,320
So, do you know
who put the money in the bag?

89
00:08:07,160 --> 00:08:08,720
I don't know.

90
00:08:08,800 --> 00:08:11,360
But Mr. Sonrak and I
were together the whole time.

91
00:08:12,040 --> 00:08:14,160
If he had put the money in her bag,

92
00:08:14,240 --> 00:08:15,680
I would've seen it.

93
00:08:20,080 --> 00:08:22,160
Maria, how would you have seen it?

94
00:08:22,240 --> 00:08:25,040
You weren't even here when I put it in.

95
00:08:30,360 --> 00:08:33,159
So, why did you do that?

96
00:08:34,440 --> 00:08:35,559
Well…

97
00:08:36,919 --> 00:08:38,480
Puna helped me with my outfit today.

98
00:08:38,559 --> 00:08:41,559
She picked a great outfit,
so I wanted to thank her.

99
00:08:42,400 --> 00:08:43,320
But…

100
00:08:43,400 --> 00:08:46,880
I knew she wouldn't accept money,
so I hid it in her bag

101
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:47,800
as a surprise.

102
00:08:51,960 --> 00:08:54,520
It's a reward for someone
who worked hard and did a good job.

103
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:57,280
Everyone, give Puna a round of applause!

104
00:09:07,240 --> 00:09:08,520
Puna, take it.

105
00:09:11,920 --> 00:09:14,200
This is for someone who worked hard.

106
00:09:14,280 --> 00:09:15,680
Take it.

107
00:09:20,920 --> 00:09:22,800
You're acting like a kid.

108
00:09:36,760 --> 00:09:38,280
You deserve it.

109
00:09:53,040 --> 00:09:55,960
-Ugh, Miss Maria!
-Hey.

110
00:09:56,040 --> 00:09:58,680
Stop already. You're going
to lose your voice.

111
00:09:59,720 --> 00:10:00,680
I won't stop!

112
00:10:02,840 --> 00:10:05,160
She's possessed! Oh no.

113
00:10:05,240 --> 00:10:07,280
-What's wrong with you?
-My earwax is dripping.

114
00:10:07,360 --> 00:10:10,000
-Ugh, it smells!
-You idiot! Go away!

115
00:10:12,480 --> 00:10:14,840
Why does Mr. Sonrak have to defend her?

116
00:10:14,920 --> 00:10:16,680
Why? Why?!

117
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:20,520
Yeah, I risked my life

118
00:10:20,600 --> 00:10:23,160
to sneak the money into her bag.

119
00:10:23,240 --> 00:10:26,720
I really don't get it.
Why is Mr. Sonrak doing this?

120
00:10:28,040 --> 00:10:29,960
-What's wrong?
-What?

121
00:10:30,040 --> 00:10:32,320
Or maybe…

122
00:10:32,400 --> 00:10:33,280
Or maybe what?

123
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:36,640
I don't want to say. It's not appropriate.

124
00:10:36,720 --> 00:10:38,400
-Just say it!
-It's hard to say.

125
00:10:38,480 --> 00:10:40,680
-Just say it!
-Alright.

126
00:10:41,480 --> 00:10:43,200
Give me some tissue.

127
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:46,680
Hold on. What if…

128
00:10:48,640 --> 00:10:50,520
What if Mr. Sonrak loves Puna?

129
00:10:50,600 --> 00:10:52,400
What if Mr. Sonrak loves Puna?

130
00:10:52,480 --> 00:10:54,520
What if Mr. Sonrak loves Puna?

131
00:10:54,600 --> 00:10:56,360
Stop. Stop!

132
00:10:58,160 --> 00:10:59,000
That could be true.

133
00:11:01,120 --> 00:11:03,000
I knew it.

134
00:11:04,280 --> 00:11:07,760
We can't let this happen.
If she became Darathong's daughter-in-law,

135
00:11:07,840 --> 00:11:09,000
we can't allow that.

136
00:11:09,080 --> 00:11:13,320
Right! If Puna marries Mr. Sonrak,

137
00:11:13,400 --> 00:11:14,840
she'll be our boss!

138
00:11:14,920 --> 00:11:16,040
Oh no.

139
00:11:16,120 --> 00:11:19,640
I won't allow it! I won't allow it!

140
00:11:19,720 --> 00:11:21,040
We need to stop her to prevent that.

141
00:11:21,120 --> 00:11:23,400
We have to stop Puna!

142
00:11:23,480 --> 00:11:24,360
Exactly!

143
00:11:24,440 --> 00:11:25,320
Fine!

144
00:11:27,760 --> 00:11:31,360
I'll never let Puna outshine me.

145
00:11:39,040 --> 00:11:41,520
-Mr. Sonrak.
-Yes?

146
00:11:43,120 --> 00:11:45,560
I really can't accept this money.

147
00:11:46,160 --> 00:11:47,720
Why not?

148
00:11:48,320 --> 00:11:51,600
About what happened earlier,
you covered for me, didn't you?

149
00:11:52,640 --> 00:11:55,640
The truth is, your money
really is missing, right?

150
00:11:55,720 --> 00:11:59,240
Yes, my money is missing,
but do you have any idea

151
00:11:59,320 --> 00:12:02,480
who took advantage of the chaos
to steal it?

152
00:12:03,360 --> 00:12:04,920
I don't know.

153
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:07,760
But I can assure you, I didn't do it.

154
00:12:07,840 --> 00:12:10,560
Why would someone do that?
What do they want?

155
00:12:11,360 --> 00:12:12,240
Well…

156
00:12:13,040 --> 00:12:15,880
Just scheming and framing me.

157
00:12:16,480 --> 00:12:19,760
If someone was willing to risk
stealing my money during the fire,

158
00:12:19,840 --> 00:12:22,040
they must really hate you.

159
00:12:23,160 --> 00:12:24,040
Don't you think so?

160
00:12:27,200 --> 00:12:29,240
And if I hadn't stepped in for you,

161
00:12:31,400 --> 00:12:33,000
what do you think would've happened?

162
00:12:33,640 --> 00:12:35,480
I would've been fired

163
00:12:35,560 --> 00:12:37,280
and probably handed over to the police.

164
00:12:38,720 --> 00:12:40,640
I really feel bad

165
00:12:40,720 --> 00:12:43,400
that you had to cover for me like this.

166
00:12:43,480 --> 00:12:45,440
The reason I defended you

167
00:12:45,520 --> 00:12:49,080
is because I believe you.
I believe you didn't steal the money.

168
00:12:49,160 --> 00:12:51,960
But if you keep trying to prove the truth,

169
00:12:52,960 --> 00:12:54,840
you'll never clear your name

170
00:12:56,240 --> 00:12:58,240
because the evidence points to you.

171
00:13:01,800 --> 00:13:04,080
And more importantly, Puna…

172
00:13:06,680 --> 00:13:07,800
Do you know…

173
00:13:09,800 --> 00:13:13,040
Do you know that…

174
00:13:16,600 --> 00:13:17,960
I like you?

175
00:13:25,200 --> 00:13:27,120
I've liked you from the very beginning,

176
00:13:28,400 --> 00:13:30,080
ever since I first saw you.

177
00:13:30,160 --> 00:13:34,240
<i>I've waited…</i>

178
00:13:34,320 --> 00:13:35,280
Who is she, Chang?

179
00:13:35,360 --> 00:13:36,720
A new singer, Boss.

180
00:13:36,800 --> 00:13:38,840
I heard she's from Nern Samran.

181
00:13:39,680 --> 00:13:40,760
She asked to sing tonight.

182
00:13:46,440 --> 00:13:47,560
And then,

183
00:13:48,520 --> 00:13:50,200
I had the chance to get closer to you.

184
00:13:52,120 --> 00:13:54,640
Puna, please don't deny my feelings.

185
00:13:57,880 --> 00:14:01,640
But I really don't think of you that way.

186
00:14:02,280 --> 00:14:03,720
Maybe not now,

187
00:14:05,160 --> 00:14:08,520
but if you give me a chance,
things might be different in the future.

188
00:14:12,520 --> 00:14:13,880
Please, Puna.

189
00:14:25,760 --> 00:14:28,400
Let me prove myself, Puna.
Please give me a chance.

190
00:14:30,640 --> 00:14:31,480
Please.

191
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:19,040
I'm sorry, Mr. Sonrak,

192
00:15:19,120 --> 00:15:22,320
but I promised Uncle Tharin

193
00:15:22,400 --> 00:15:25,640
that I wouldn't think about a boyfriend
until I achieve my goal.

194
00:15:26,920 --> 00:15:30,360
Achieve your goal? What goal, Puna?

195
00:15:31,160 --> 00:15:34,440
Well, to become a singer.

196
00:15:35,040 --> 00:15:37,480
My goal is to become a singer.

197
00:15:37,560 --> 00:15:41,040
As long as I'm not a singer yet,

198
00:15:41,120 --> 00:15:42,880
I won't think about having a boyfriend.

199
00:15:42,960 --> 00:15:44,600
Alright.

200
00:15:44,680 --> 00:15:47,400
I'll make sure you become a singer
as soon as possible.

201
00:15:48,200 --> 00:15:49,240
But you have to promise me,

202
00:15:49,320 --> 00:15:51,200
once you become a singer,

203
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:55,760
you'll give me a chance.

204
00:16:02,520 --> 00:16:04,400
It's time for the second livestream.

205
00:16:06,040 --> 00:16:07,400
I know.

206
00:16:10,120 --> 00:16:11,200
Don't forget, Puna.

207
00:16:11,920 --> 00:16:14,160
The day you become a singer,

208
00:16:15,200 --> 00:16:16,520
I'll come to claim my promise.

209
00:17:00,160 --> 00:17:01,800
Wait, rewind a bit.

210
00:17:07,839 --> 00:17:08,800
Come in.

211
00:17:14,960 --> 00:17:17,720
You called us. Is there something up, sir?

212
00:17:17,800 --> 00:17:19,760
What were you two supposed to do today?

213
00:17:20,480 --> 00:17:22,400
Why are you here
before the scheduled time?

214
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:26,359
We're the livestreaming team,
so we need to prepare in advance.

215
00:17:26,440 --> 00:17:29,480
The footage from the CCTV
disappeared for a while. Who did that?

216
00:17:30,840 --> 00:17:32,880
It definitely wasn't us.
Why would we do that?

217
00:17:36,440 --> 00:17:37,280
Then what's this?

218
00:17:37,960 --> 00:17:38,800
Huh?

219
00:17:44,840 --> 00:17:46,160
I don't see the face here.

220
00:17:48,080 --> 00:17:49,360
But at that time,

221
00:17:50,280 --> 00:17:52,440
you two were the only ones
in the building.

222
00:17:55,200 --> 00:17:59,080
Yes, but we were preparing in the studio.

223
00:17:59,160 --> 00:18:01,560
The person in the footage
definitely wasn't us.

224
00:18:02,920 --> 00:18:05,240
I think the person who unplugged it

225
00:18:05,320 --> 00:18:07,160
must be the one who started the fire.

226
00:18:07,760 --> 00:18:09,280
Exactly.

227
00:18:09,360 --> 00:18:12,480
They unplugged it to start the fire

228
00:18:12,560 --> 00:18:14,960
and didn't want anyone to see their face.

229
00:18:18,760 --> 00:18:21,080
-May I come in?
-Come in.

230
00:18:21,880 --> 00:18:22,800
What's up?

231
00:18:23,560 --> 00:18:24,880
I got something.

232
00:18:26,640 --> 00:18:30,280
I asked to see the CCTV footage
from the store behind the company.

233
00:18:30,360 --> 00:18:32,320
It shows the culprits.

234
00:18:32,400 --> 00:18:34,880
The two of them
were carrying gasoline cans.

235
00:18:36,800 --> 00:18:39,240
Who are they? Do we know them?

236
00:18:39,320 --> 00:18:41,960
Yes, Boss. One is Weerachai.

237
00:18:42,040 --> 00:18:43,160
His subordinate is named Jan.

238
00:18:51,680 --> 00:18:52,560
Jan.

239
00:18:54,480 --> 00:18:56,960
I want you to help catch the culprits
who set the fire

240
00:18:57,040 --> 00:18:58,320
to the record label for me.

241
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:00,400
Do you already know who they are?

242
00:19:01,360 --> 00:19:02,680
I'll send you the photos.

243
00:19:03,360 --> 00:19:04,880
Their names are Weerachai and Jan.

244
00:19:05,600 --> 00:19:07,680
Alright, I'll take care of it right away.

245
00:19:08,680 --> 00:19:09,640
Thank you.

246
00:19:16,400 --> 00:19:19,160
Sure, Auntie. I'll handle it
within seven days.

247
00:19:19,240 --> 00:19:20,120
Okay.

248
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:21,960
Thank you.

249
00:19:28,600 --> 00:19:30,240
You're Weerachai from Nong Na village

250
00:19:31,320 --> 00:19:32,160
and Jan, right?

251
00:19:32,240 --> 00:19:33,960
Is there something wrong, Officer?

252
00:19:34,040 --> 00:19:35,400
You're under arrest.

253
00:19:37,720 --> 00:19:40,040
For the charge of arson
and property damage.

254
00:19:42,880 --> 00:19:44,480
What's this, Officer?

255
00:19:44,560 --> 00:19:46,320
You've got the wrong person.

256
00:19:46,400 --> 00:19:47,800
I haven't done anything.

257
00:19:48,400 --> 00:19:51,080
Don't worry. We've got all the evidence.

258
00:19:51,160 --> 00:19:52,520
Let's talk more at the station.

259
00:19:57,640 --> 00:19:59,520
Hey, Officer.

260
00:19:59,600 --> 00:20:01,720
How could this be me? I didn't--

261
00:20:01,800 --> 00:20:03,640
-Hey, let's go!
-Chase them!

262
00:20:03,720 --> 00:20:05,000
Hey, stop!

263
00:20:09,360 --> 00:20:11,000
Faster!

264
00:20:11,080 --> 00:20:12,040
Stop right there!

265
00:20:14,400 --> 00:20:15,440
-Arrest them!
-Stop!

266
00:20:18,760 --> 00:20:19,840
Let go!

267
00:20:24,800 --> 00:20:25,640
Take them to the station.

268
00:20:31,520 --> 00:20:33,920
Weerachai! This is bad.

269
00:20:34,840 --> 00:20:36,360
-Let go of me!
-Go!

270
00:20:43,360 --> 00:20:45,360
Make sure you deliver the goods on time.

271
00:20:46,440 --> 00:20:48,840
Boss, something happened!

272
00:20:48,920 --> 00:20:50,080
What's wrong with you, Khod?

273
00:20:51,720 --> 00:20:54,160
-Well…
-What do you want to say?!

274
00:20:54,960 --> 00:20:57,800
Weerachai and his man
have been arrested by the police.

275
00:20:57,880 --> 00:20:59,760
What does that have to do with me?

276
00:20:59,840 --> 00:21:03,680
But he is the one we sent
to start the fire, Boss.

277
00:21:05,680 --> 00:21:07,560
Someone like him,

278
00:21:07,640 --> 00:21:11,200
I think he'll talk
and trace everything back to you.

279
00:21:16,920 --> 00:21:18,120
Pleaw.

280
00:21:18,200 --> 00:21:21,280
You go take care of him.
Make sure he doesn't say too much.

281
00:21:21,880 --> 00:21:22,720
Understood, Boss.

282
00:21:37,640 --> 00:21:39,760
Manat, we've got a problem!

283
00:21:39,840 --> 00:21:41,160
What problem?

284
00:21:41,760 --> 00:21:43,360
Weerachai is about to be silenced.

285
00:21:43,440 --> 00:21:45,440
-Boss Noo?
-Yeah.

286
00:21:45,520 --> 00:21:48,560
He's afraid Weerachai will talk,
so he plans to get rid of him.

287
00:21:48,640 --> 00:21:51,680
If he gets taken out,
we'll lose an important witness.

288
00:21:52,280 --> 00:21:53,720
Let's go. Hurry up.

289
00:22:15,400 --> 00:22:17,520
Pull over. Sergeant,
get out and check it out.

290
00:22:17,600 --> 00:22:18,720
Yes, sir.

291
00:22:23,200 --> 00:22:24,240
Turn off the engine.

292
00:22:28,800 --> 00:22:29,920
What's wrong with the car?

293
00:23:01,760 --> 00:23:02,600
Let's go!

294
00:23:35,120 --> 00:23:36,240
Go! Retreat!

295
00:23:55,640 --> 00:23:56,760
Is anyone hurt?

296
00:23:57,360 --> 00:23:58,200
No.

297
00:23:59,120 --> 00:24:01,120
Where did you two get those guns?

298
00:24:01,200 --> 00:24:02,520
Do you even have permits?

299
00:24:03,200 --> 00:24:05,280
Wow, strict much?

300
00:24:05,360 --> 00:24:07,000
They're my guns, Captain.

301
00:24:07,920 --> 00:24:10,640
I called these two to come help you.

302
00:24:10,720 --> 00:24:12,480
Their house is nearby.

303
00:24:13,480 --> 00:24:15,640
Don't go after them. They're my nephews.

304
00:24:18,040 --> 00:24:18,960
Fine.

305
00:24:20,040 --> 00:24:23,800
I'll let you two off this time.
Don't think about using guns illegally.

306
00:24:24,720 --> 00:24:26,840
I'll be keeping an eye on both of you.

307
00:24:27,560 --> 00:24:30,840
Yes, Captain. If I don't have to,
I'll stay away from guns.

308
00:24:31,440 --> 00:24:34,760
Same here. I promise I won't touch them.

309
00:24:38,440 --> 00:24:40,440
Weerachai and Jan can't have gotten far.

310
00:24:40,520 --> 00:24:42,520
Spread out and search the whole area.

311
00:24:42,600 --> 00:24:43,440
-Yes, sir.
-Sergeant Yot.

312
00:24:43,520 --> 00:24:45,680
Tell the backup team
to set up a roadblock.

313
00:24:45,760 --> 00:24:46,840
Yes, sir.

314
00:24:49,240 --> 00:24:50,520
Anything we can help with?

315
00:24:51,880 --> 00:24:54,200
No, you guys stay out of this.

316
00:24:55,320 --> 00:24:58,560
Come on, Chaiya.
He doesn't want us involved.

317
00:25:09,840 --> 00:25:11,360
Is anyone following us, Jan?

318
00:25:12,320 --> 00:25:13,440
I don't think so.

319
00:25:19,920 --> 00:25:21,080
Khod! Hey!

320
00:25:25,360 --> 00:25:27,200
Thought it was someone else,
but it's you, Khod.

321
00:25:28,200 --> 00:25:31,560
Yeah. Wait here.
The car will pick you up soon.

322
00:25:31,640 --> 00:25:34,160
Help me out. Take me with you.

323
00:25:35,240 --> 00:25:37,880
Of course. I got you covered.

324
00:25:54,800 --> 00:25:55,720
Jan!

325
00:25:55,800 --> 00:25:57,200
No!

326
00:26:00,160 --> 00:26:01,240
That direction. Let's go!

327
00:26:17,880 --> 00:26:18,720
You're dead!

328
00:26:24,240 --> 00:26:25,160
Stop!

329
00:26:40,360 --> 00:26:41,320
Go!

330
00:26:45,640 --> 00:26:47,000
Uncle!

331
00:26:55,280 --> 00:26:56,640
Uncle!

332
00:26:56,720 --> 00:26:59,320
Uncle Sergeant! Uncle!

333
00:26:59,400 --> 00:27:00,720
Sergeant.

334
00:27:01,880 --> 00:27:03,600
Stay true to your duty.

335
00:27:04,640 --> 00:27:05,960
Be an honest cop.

336
00:27:07,840 --> 00:27:10,520
I'm really proud of you.

337
00:27:15,480 --> 00:27:17,720
Uncle! Uncle!

338
00:27:18,600 --> 00:27:19,680
Uncle!

339
00:27:27,160 --> 00:27:28,000
He's gone.

340
00:27:36,200 --> 00:27:37,160
Uncle…

341
00:28:02,320 --> 00:28:03,400
I never expected

342
00:28:04,480 --> 00:28:06,600
that our operation

343
00:28:06,680 --> 00:28:09,280
would result in such an unexpected loss.

344
00:28:09,880 --> 00:28:11,160
I promise

345
00:28:12,240 --> 00:28:15,240
I'll wipe them out completely.

346
00:28:20,040 --> 00:28:21,480
I spoke with the higher-ups last night.

347
00:28:22,840 --> 00:28:25,000
From the evidence we sent,

348
00:28:25,920 --> 00:28:28,880
it's circumstantial. We're missing
the physical evidence.

349
00:28:32,080 --> 00:28:35,480
Once we have the evidence and the source,

350
00:28:36,800 --> 00:28:38,600
we can take them down immediately.

351
00:28:42,240 --> 00:28:44,200
We need to take them down, Chaiya.

352
00:28:46,600 --> 00:28:48,480
To honor Uncle Sergeant's spirit.

353
00:28:49,000 --> 00:28:50,080
Yes.

354
00:28:51,800 --> 00:28:53,560
His death

355
00:28:55,160 --> 00:28:56,680
will not be in vain.

356
00:29:11,960 --> 00:29:15,360
Stop the car. Stop!

357
00:29:16,280 --> 00:29:18,600
Roll down the window.

358
00:29:21,880 --> 00:29:23,560
Hey! This is Maria,

359
00:29:24,640 --> 00:29:26,880
the singer from this label.
What do you want to check?

360
00:29:28,680 --> 00:29:31,040
Is there a problem?
Why check people going in and out?

361
00:29:31,120 --> 00:29:33,760
The company was just attacked by arson.

362
00:29:33,840 --> 00:29:34,960
The boss ordered the checks.

363
00:29:35,520 --> 00:29:36,880
Sorry about that, Miss Maria.

364
00:29:36,960 --> 00:29:38,680
-Please go ahead.
-Go ahead. My apologies.

365
00:29:46,360 --> 00:29:52,680
DARATHONG MUSIC

366
00:29:59,880 --> 00:30:01,320
Why did you bring me here?

367
00:30:02,200 --> 00:30:04,640
I want you to talk to Mr. Singha

368
00:30:04,720 --> 00:30:07,840
about me and Mr. Sonrak.

369
00:30:09,720 --> 00:30:10,800
You think he'll agree?

370
00:30:12,160 --> 00:30:13,640
He'll have to.

371
00:30:13,720 --> 00:30:15,760
Otherwise, I won't get famous.

372
00:30:19,280 --> 00:30:20,720
And where are you guys going now?

373
00:30:20,800 --> 00:30:22,960
Today, Mr. Sonrak

374
00:30:23,040 --> 00:30:25,760
is trying on clothes at Kook Kai's studio.

375
00:30:25,840 --> 00:30:27,560
Miss Maria has to follow up.

376
00:30:27,640 --> 00:30:28,880
Follow up? Why?

377
00:30:29,480 --> 00:30:31,120
You know, to take photos together

378
00:30:31,200 --> 00:30:34,600
for social media, showing
that they make a good couple.

379
00:30:34,680 --> 00:30:38,040
That way, Miss Maria can ride on his fame.

380
00:30:43,040 --> 00:30:45,320
Okay, great.

381
00:30:46,040 --> 00:30:47,520
-Then I'll go ahead.
-Wait.

382
00:30:48,120 --> 00:30:49,560
Dad, make it happen.

383
00:30:49,640 --> 00:30:50,640
Got it.

384
00:30:55,840 --> 00:30:56,920
Yes!

385
00:30:58,040 --> 00:31:00,000
Let's go!

386
00:31:06,080 --> 00:31:07,480
What did you say, Village Head?

387
00:31:07,560 --> 00:31:10,720
You want Sonrak
to direct the MV for Maria?

388
00:31:11,440 --> 00:31:15,040
Yes, that's right. Right now,
the social media buzz

389
00:31:15,120 --> 00:31:19,040
is all about the MV
for "I Want to Be Famous" by Maria.

390
00:31:19,120 --> 00:31:22,360
I think if we want to make
this song grab attention,

391
00:31:22,440 --> 00:31:24,520
we should have Mr. Sonrak

392
00:31:25,680 --> 00:31:27,320
be the one to direct it, boss.

393
00:31:28,520 --> 00:31:30,840
But he has never directed an MV.

394
00:31:31,520 --> 00:31:34,840
He only does YouTube content.
Will it really work?

395
00:31:34,920 --> 00:31:38,080
Let the real director
handle the actual directing.

396
00:31:38,160 --> 00:31:40,440
But when it comes to the media coverage,

397
00:31:41,080 --> 00:31:42,240
let Mr. Sonrak

398
00:31:42,880 --> 00:31:44,680
pretend to act

399
00:31:44,760 --> 00:31:46,840
like he's directing it.

400
00:31:46,920 --> 00:31:48,680
And then,

401
00:31:48,760 --> 00:31:52,200
we can use it for promotion
and get more likes.

402
00:31:53,400 --> 00:31:54,680
This sounds like a good plan.

403
00:31:54,760 --> 00:31:56,440
This way,

404
00:31:56,520 --> 00:31:58,600
we promote the MV

405
00:32:00,080 --> 00:32:01,360
and also

406
00:32:01,440 --> 00:32:05,400
highlight Mr. Sonrak's talent
at the same time.

407
00:32:07,800 --> 00:32:10,040
I think you shouldn't hesitate.

408
00:32:10,120 --> 00:32:13,000
Let's go with what I've suggested.

409
00:32:13,080 --> 00:32:14,160
Okay?

410
00:32:19,560 --> 00:32:20,560
I'll buy the idea.

411
00:32:22,240 --> 00:32:23,760
You're sharp, Village Head.

412
00:32:23,840 --> 00:32:26,320
Are you saying I'm a sharp head

413
00:32:26,400 --> 00:32:27,880
with a slippery touch?

414
00:32:29,560 --> 00:32:31,600
I didn't say that. You said it yourself!

415
00:32:34,280 --> 00:32:35,520
It's sharp,

416
00:32:37,160 --> 00:32:38,400
but slippery.

417
00:32:42,280 --> 00:32:43,200
Hey.

418
00:32:44,880 --> 00:32:47,920
Where's the entrance to the studio?

419
00:32:48,000 --> 00:32:51,360
Joey, don't forget,
you're in charge of the camera.

420
00:32:51,440 --> 00:32:53,440
Secretly film Mr. Sonrak and Miss Maria

421
00:32:53,520 --> 00:32:54,920
when they're close to each other.

422
00:32:55,000 --> 00:32:57,880
After that, send it to me.
I'll upload it to social media.

423
00:32:57,960 --> 00:32:59,040
Got it.

424
00:33:00,000 --> 00:33:04,040
Manat said Mr. Sonrak is trying on
sponsor clothes at Kook Kai's studio.

425
00:33:05,680 --> 00:33:08,240
But there are so many rooms.
Which one is it?

426
00:33:09,640 --> 00:33:11,520
His assistants are over there.

427
00:33:13,200 --> 00:33:14,160
Hey.

428
00:33:15,120 --> 00:33:16,680
Why are Maria and her team here?

429
00:33:17,360 --> 00:33:18,360
You'll find out soon.

430
00:33:19,600 --> 00:33:23,280
Excuse me. Where's the entrance
to the studio?

431
00:33:24,240 --> 00:33:27,400
Well, it's this way.
Mr. Sonrak is inside.

432
00:33:35,200 --> 00:33:37,000
Let's hurry inside, Miss Maria.

433
00:33:52,040 --> 00:33:54,080
-Can I have the pin?
-Here you go.

434
00:33:56,280 --> 00:33:58,400
-And the measuring tape?
-Here it is.

435
00:33:59,400 --> 00:34:00,880
Thanks.

436
00:34:03,120 --> 00:34:04,800
What a coincidence!

437
00:34:04,880 --> 00:34:07,240
I didn't expect to see you here.

438
00:34:07,320 --> 00:34:09,760
What brings you here, Maria?

439
00:34:09,840 --> 00:34:11,560
I was just visiting a friend in the area.

440
00:34:11,639 --> 00:34:15,239
I heard someone from Darathong Music
was trying on clothes,

441
00:34:15,320 --> 00:34:17,000
but I didn't expect it to be you.

442
00:34:17,080 --> 00:34:18,560
That's right.

443
00:34:19,080 --> 00:34:23,040
Wow, this jacket is beautiful!

444
00:34:23,120 --> 00:34:25,120
Can I take a closer look?

445
00:34:26,360 --> 00:34:28,840
Oh, this is really beautiful.

446
00:34:28,920 --> 00:34:30,360
It suits you so well!

447
00:34:30,440 --> 00:34:32,960
May I ask who the designer is?

448
00:34:33,840 --> 00:34:35,199
It's from Marga Lupin,

449
00:34:35,280 --> 00:34:38,520
a French designer.

450
00:34:38,600 --> 00:34:43,239
The client wanted Mr. Sonrak
to wear this and look good,

451
00:34:43,320 --> 00:34:45,639
so we had him try it on first.

452
00:34:45,719 --> 00:34:49,199
On the actual day,
he will look so stylish in it.

453
00:34:50,719 --> 00:34:51,800
Is it very expensive?

454
00:34:52,880 --> 00:34:54,360
Very expensive.

455
00:34:55,679 --> 00:34:59,640
And it's a collectible item too.

456
00:35:00,240 --> 00:35:02,880
The owner is very protective of it.

457
00:35:02,960 --> 00:35:05,240
That's not even including the accessories.

458
00:35:05,320 --> 00:35:07,320
I can guarantee…

459
00:35:08,240 --> 00:35:10,880
it costs a fortune.

460
00:35:12,360 --> 00:35:15,240
I don't even dare to touch it.

461
00:35:15,320 --> 00:35:17,880
Puna, make sure you take good care

462
00:35:17,960 --> 00:35:19,880
of the clothes.

463
00:35:19,960 --> 00:35:22,040
If anything happens to it,

464
00:35:22,120 --> 00:35:24,440
you won't be able to pay for it.

465
00:35:25,640 --> 00:35:26,560
Exactly.

466
00:35:27,680 --> 00:35:29,160
Mr. Sonrak.

467
00:35:29,240 --> 00:35:30,880
-Please take it off in that room.
-Sure.

468
00:35:30,960 --> 00:35:33,440
-Let me help you.
-No need.

469
00:35:34,120 --> 00:35:35,800
Mr. Sonrak's clothes

470
00:35:35,880 --> 00:35:38,040
are very expensive.
We need to take extra care of them,

471
00:35:38,120 --> 00:35:41,280
more than regular clothes.

472
00:35:41,360 --> 00:35:42,760
No need, thank you.

473
00:35:45,120 --> 00:35:46,080
Let me see.

474
00:35:48,760 --> 00:35:52,840
Puna, can you prepare several outfits
for me when we get back to the office?

475
00:35:53,360 --> 00:35:54,360
What for?

476
00:35:56,120 --> 00:35:58,320
I'm going to shoot a music video.

477
00:35:59,000 --> 00:36:01,560
I'd like to have
some beautiful, new outfits

478
00:36:01,640 --> 00:36:02,800
to wear.

479
00:36:06,880 --> 00:36:10,160
Miss Maria, is that really a good idea?

480
00:36:10,240 --> 00:36:13,320
Can Puna do it?
She's just a laundry girl.

481
00:36:14,040 --> 00:36:17,440
Is it okay to have her take care
of the artist's wardrobe?

482
00:36:17,520 --> 00:36:19,640
Why, Sophie?

483
00:36:20,240 --> 00:36:23,240
-I'm not burying her, but…
-Bully.

484
00:36:24,480 --> 00:36:27,000
-Bully.
-Bully?

485
00:36:27,080 --> 00:36:29,080
I'm not bullying her.

486
00:36:29,960 --> 00:36:31,560
Puna is just a laundry girl.

487
00:36:32,240 --> 00:36:35,640
When she handles an artist's wardrobe,
it might look like a trip to a market

488
00:36:35,720 --> 00:36:36,680
or a temple.

489
00:36:36,760 --> 00:36:39,040
It's not really appropriate.
You're an artist!

490
00:36:39,120 --> 00:36:41,960
-Oh right, I am a singer now.
-Yes.

491
00:36:42,040 --> 00:36:44,560
Guess I need a stylist, then.

492
00:36:44,640 --> 00:36:45,520
How about this?

493
00:36:45,600 --> 00:36:48,760
I'll check with Kook Kai's studio

494
00:36:48,840 --> 00:36:51,320
for an available designer.
How about the one from earlier?

495
00:36:51,400 --> 00:36:53,120
-Good.
-Okay?

496
00:36:53,200 --> 00:36:56,080
Let's leave now.
It smells so musty in here.

497
00:36:57,320 --> 00:36:59,160
-Alright? Let's go.
-Let's go now.

498
00:36:59,240 --> 00:37:00,560
We're out.

499
00:37:02,000 --> 00:37:03,800
Wow!

500
00:37:03,880 --> 00:37:04,880
Let's go.

501
00:37:08,840 --> 00:37:11,320
What's wrong, Puna? You look so sad.

502
00:37:16,880 --> 00:37:19,440
Maria's about to shoot her music video.

503
00:37:20,160 --> 00:37:21,480
But look at me.

504
00:37:23,640 --> 00:37:26,160
I'm still just the girl
handling the clothes.

505
00:37:27,320 --> 00:37:29,920
It's okay. Just wait a little longer.

506
00:37:30,000 --> 00:37:31,760
Your opportunity will come.

507
00:37:32,360 --> 00:37:35,080
But I already asked
the songwriters, Teacher.

508
00:37:35,160 --> 00:37:36,840
What did they say?

509
00:37:38,480 --> 00:37:41,920
Mr. Singha hasn't asked them
to write a song for me yet.

510
00:37:43,120 --> 00:37:46,640
He's only asked for the second
and third songs for Maria.

511
00:37:47,720 --> 00:37:50,000
Hey, how about a song from me?

512
00:37:51,160 --> 00:37:52,760
I can write one for you.

513
00:37:55,680 --> 00:37:57,360
That would be great, Teacher.

514
00:37:57,440 --> 00:37:59,240
What kind of song do you want?

515
00:37:59,320 --> 00:38:03,200
Can you give me an example
of your favorite song to use as a guide?

516
00:38:06,120 --> 00:38:09,480
There's one song I used
to listen to when I was a kid.

517
00:38:10,080 --> 00:38:12,280
-Uncle Tharin used to play it for me.
-Yes.

518
00:38:12,960 --> 00:38:16,360
It's by a female singer.

519
00:38:18,320 --> 00:38:19,840
What's her name, Puna?

520
00:38:21,080 --> 00:38:22,480
I don't know the name.

521
00:38:22,560 --> 00:38:24,680
I have no idea who sings it.

522
00:38:24,760 --> 00:38:27,920
When I asked Uncle Tharin who sang it,
he wouldn't tell me.

523
00:38:30,320 --> 00:38:32,920
All I remember is that it was
on an old cassette tape

524
00:38:33,600 --> 00:38:35,480
that he was really protective of.

525
00:38:35,560 --> 00:38:38,000
He wouldn't let anyone play it,
afraid it would get damaged.

526
00:38:39,280 --> 00:38:42,240
Well, then try singing it for me.

527
00:38:44,440 --> 00:38:46,600
Maybe I'll remember

528
00:38:46,680 --> 00:38:48,760
the name or who sang it.

529
00:38:50,640 --> 00:38:51,680
Okay.

530
00:38:56,600 --> 00:39:01,360
<i>Back then, my heart was strong</i>

531
00:39:03,800 --> 00:39:10,080
<i>As tough as a bar of steel</i>

532
00:39:11,320 --> 00:39:16,960
<i>So many men chased after me</i>

533
00:39:17,040 --> 00:39:20,680
<i>But I never paid them any mind</i>

534
00:39:20,760 --> 00:39:25,080
<i>Never gave them a thought</i>

535
00:39:27,320 --> 00:39:29,360
That was amazing, Puna.

536
00:39:30,080 --> 00:39:31,040
Thanks.

537
00:39:33,920 --> 00:39:36,400
Teacher, is something wrong? Are you okay?

538
00:39:36,480 --> 00:39:37,800
Nothing's wrong.

539
00:39:38,760 --> 00:39:41,800
-Why do you look like you're going to cry?
-No.

540
00:39:44,120 --> 00:39:45,160
I'm not crying.

541
00:39:46,840 --> 00:39:49,040
I just feel bad for you.

542
00:39:49,120 --> 00:39:51,040
No one has written a song
for you to sing yet.

543
00:39:52,720 --> 00:39:54,280
Don't cry, Teacher.

544
00:39:56,000 --> 00:39:58,680
So, will you write a song for me?

545
00:39:59,680 --> 00:40:02,560
I'd like something
like the one I just sang.

546
00:40:05,760 --> 00:40:06,720
Teacher.

547
00:40:07,680 --> 00:40:10,320
Do you know what the song is called?

548
00:40:10,960 --> 00:40:13,280
The song is called "Soft Heart".

549
00:40:14,640 --> 00:40:15,760
"Soft Heart"?

550
00:40:16,800 --> 00:40:19,200
You know this song? Who sings it?

551
00:40:28,400 --> 00:40:30,480
You don't need to worry about that yet.

552
00:40:31,080 --> 00:40:33,520
Let's just say
I'll use this song as inspiration.

553
00:40:34,880 --> 00:40:37,600
I'll try to write
something like it for you.

554
00:40:42,040 --> 00:40:44,120
Thank you so much, Teacher.

555
00:40:44,200 --> 00:40:46,320
I'll do my best to sing it perfectly.

556
00:40:48,720 --> 00:40:50,920
Don't cry.

557
00:40:52,520 --> 00:40:56,280
You're my strong teacher. You won't cry.

558
00:41:02,800 --> 00:41:03,640
Puna.

559
00:41:05,320 --> 00:41:06,200
Let me help.

560
00:41:07,640 --> 00:41:08,680
Thanks.

561
00:41:11,080 --> 00:41:12,320
Are you tired?

562
00:41:12,400 --> 00:41:14,160
Not at all. Are you not going back yet?

563
00:41:15,160 --> 00:41:17,000
Mr. Sonrak is still finishing up
some work.

564
00:41:18,720 --> 00:41:22,160
Chaiya, I'm really sorry
about Uncle Sergeant.

565
00:41:24,920 --> 00:41:25,960
Thanks.

566
00:41:27,160 --> 00:41:31,200
Now that he's not around anymore,
are you still going to stay here?

567
00:41:33,160 --> 00:41:37,640
Of course, my job and income are here,
so I have to stay.

568
00:41:40,440 --> 00:41:41,600
Oh, Chaiya.

569
00:41:42,880 --> 00:41:45,920
Teacher, I've memorized
all the lyrics you wrote for me.

570
00:41:49,280 --> 00:41:50,280
What lyrics?

571
00:41:51,840 --> 00:41:54,400
Well, I wrote them for him.

572
00:41:56,880 --> 00:41:58,360
You can sing?

573
00:42:00,720 --> 00:42:02,080
Not really.

574
00:42:02,160 --> 00:42:04,840
I just really like the song he wrote,
so I asked to sing it.

575
00:42:06,280 --> 00:42:08,520
Don't be so humble, Chaiya.

576
00:42:08,600 --> 00:42:10,360
You sing really well!

577
00:42:10,440 --> 00:42:14,640
Just practice a little more,
and you'll sound great.

578
00:42:16,360 --> 00:42:19,760
Come on. Let me hear it.

579
00:42:21,160 --> 00:42:24,120
No, I'll save it for later.
I'm not ready to sing for you yet.

580
00:42:25,040 --> 00:42:26,440
Chaiya.

581
00:42:28,880 --> 00:42:30,880
You need to take the stuff
to the office, right?

582
00:42:32,560 --> 00:42:33,600
Thanks.

583
00:42:34,480 --> 00:42:36,360
Let's split for now.
See you at the office.

584
00:42:51,720 --> 00:42:53,920
Puna, you really are popular.

585
00:42:54,520 --> 00:42:56,840
Both the boss and the assistant

586
00:42:56,920 --> 00:42:58,640
keep trying to get
your attention every day.

587
00:42:59,800 --> 00:43:04,360
I'm not thinking about that right now.
I'm not ready.

588
00:43:05,040 --> 00:43:07,920
-Really?
-Yes, really.

589
00:43:08,960 --> 00:43:11,040
I don't want to talk about it. Let's go.

590
00:43:17,960 --> 00:43:18,840
Stop!

591
00:43:21,440 --> 00:43:23,480
-We're delivering stuff.
-Who ordered it?

592
00:43:23,560 --> 00:43:24,960
The wardrobe department.

593
00:43:25,560 --> 00:43:27,000
It's clothing for the shoot.

594
00:43:27,520 --> 00:43:28,880
Let me check it first.

595
00:43:29,680 --> 00:43:31,400
Tod, Wong, go check the bags.

596
00:43:31,480 --> 00:43:32,600
-Sure.
-Got it.

597
00:43:45,480 --> 00:43:47,000
-Hey, the boss is here. Hurry!
-Chit!

598
00:43:47,720 --> 00:43:50,320
-What?
-It's nothing, just the clothes.

599
00:43:50,400 --> 00:43:52,720
Go on then. The boss is waiting.

600
00:43:52,800 --> 00:43:53,840
Let them in.

601
00:43:55,600 --> 00:43:56,640
Go!

602
00:44:07,600 --> 00:44:08,480
Everything okay?

603
00:44:08,560 --> 00:44:11,040
Yes, Boss. I've checked everyone
who's entered and left.

604
00:44:11,120 --> 00:44:12,640
Good. Let's go.

605
00:44:17,000 --> 00:44:20,120
PARKING

606
00:45:05,680 --> 00:45:07,120
Au called.

607
00:45:08,760 --> 00:45:11,200
-What's going on?
-He overheard someone planting a bomb.

608
00:45:11,800 --> 00:45:12,640
Where?

609
00:45:13,560 --> 00:45:16,000
Could it be this car?

610
00:45:16,080 --> 00:45:18,840
Probably not. We've been
watching it closely.

611
00:45:20,120 --> 00:45:22,680
Well, did he say where?

612
00:45:23,280 --> 00:45:25,240
No, he didn't give any details.

613
00:45:29,320 --> 00:45:31,680
Hey, the boss is done.

614
00:45:31,760 --> 00:45:33,880
Let's head back. Am I done for the day?

615
00:45:33,960 --> 00:45:35,320
This is your last appointment.

616
00:45:35,400 --> 00:45:36,520
Let's go.

617
00:46:03,320 --> 00:46:04,240
Go, Puna.

618
00:46:05,160 --> 00:46:06,000
Put the stuff away.

619
00:46:14,840 --> 00:46:17,560
These small bags
are pretty heavy, aren't they?

620
00:46:21,240 --> 00:46:23,880
DARATHONG STUDIO ONE

621
00:46:37,160 --> 00:46:38,320
Should I set off the bomb?

622
00:46:39,080 --> 00:46:39,920
Take it easy.

623
00:46:40,560 --> 00:46:43,920
Wait until Singha walks closer,
then we'll set it off.

624
00:46:52,360 --> 00:46:53,440
Chang.

625
00:46:54,280 --> 00:46:55,200
Stop the car.

626
00:47:02,000 --> 00:47:02,960
CHECKPOINT

627
00:47:03,040 --> 00:47:04,320
That's Mr. Sonrak's car.

628
00:47:04,960 --> 00:47:06,160
Why is he stopping?

629
00:47:07,640 --> 00:47:10,240
He might be having trouble
with Chaiya or Manat.

630
00:47:12,280 --> 00:47:15,840
Chit, something seems off.

631
00:47:17,840 --> 00:47:20,080
Chaiya, why did you stop the car?

632
00:47:20,160 --> 00:47:22,080
We're almost at the company.

633
00:47:24,720 --> 00:47:27,400
Look at that truck. They look suspicious.

634
00:47:32,920 --> 00:47:33,840
Are they waiting to ambush us?

635
00:47:36,080 --> 00:47:39,560
Hey, we should get out of here.
They're definitely going to shoot at us.

636
00:47:44,280 --> 00:47:47,000
Wait, Boss. Not sure
who left these sacks here.

637
00:47:48,840 --> 00:47:50,000
It's nothing.

638
00:47:51,120 --> 00:47:53,920
Probably from the wardrobe department.
Puna!

639
00:47:54,480 --> 00:47:55,360
Yes?

640
00:47:56,720 --> 00:47:57,960
Why are they here?

641
00:47:59,720 --> 00:48:00,920
Pick up, Dad.

642
00:48:02,320 --> 00:48:04,680
Chaiya, he's holding a remote.

643
00:48:04,760 --> 00:48:05,720
Maybe…

644
00:48:06,600 --> 00:48:08,240
they're waiting to hit the remote.

645
00:48:15,040 --> 00:48:17,640
Well, these sacks of clothes aren't ours.

646
00:48:17,720 --> 00:48:19,200
I don't know who put them here.

647
00:48:23,480 --> 00:48:25,360
What's going on? Hey, Tod, Wong!

648
00:48:25,440 --> 00:48:26,720
-Hey!
-Back off!

649
00:48:26,800 --> 00:48:28,120
-Keep guard here.
-Hey!

650
00:48:31,720 --> 00:48:34,560
Hey, Singha's coming out!

651
00:48:35,200 --> 00:48:36,880
Hey! Watch out!

652
00:48:39,680 --> 00:48:40,960
Don't get close!

653
00:48:46,400 --> 00:48:47,760
Hey!

654
00:48:49,840 --> 00:48:51,400
Everything that happened…

655
00:48:51,480 --> 00:48:52,840
NEXT EPISODE

656
00:48:52,920 --> 00:48:54,440
It's because of me!

657
00:48:56,640 --> 00:48:59,240
And Puna getting hurt like this,

658
00:48:59,320 --> 00:49:00,920
it's because of me.

659
00:49:03,320 --> 00:49:04,920
Dad is here, Puna.

660
00:49:06,400 --> 00:49:08,200
Get the guys ready.

661
00:49:08,880 --> 00:49:10,440
Go crush them.

662
00:49:10,520 --> 00:49:11,760
Got it, Boss.

663
00:49:15,120 --> 00:49:16,920
Be careful on your way back.

664
00:52:19,560 --> 00:52:21,880
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
